{
  "text": "Small post-oral breaks are typically found in aphakic retinal detachments, whereas large equatorial tears are more suggestive of myo pic detachments. [CITATION_1] We found that 50% of our cases had tears which were not typically \"aphakic\", but were not more likely to be associated with lattice or myopia which have equatorial pathology. The remaining holes were more typical of aphakic detachments (retinal holes often not being found in aphakic patients as they are small and very peripheral;",
